description: This repository offers a thorough explanation of the experiments detailed in the paper, encompassing detailed documentation of configurations, procedures, intermediate logs, and final results. Its goal is to promote transparency and reproducibility in the research process, empowering others to verify and expand upon the findings presented in the paper.
title: Repository of paper - Using Run-time Information to Enhance Static Analysis of Machine Learning Code in Notebooks
references: Yuhao Zhang, Yifan Chen, Shing-Chi Cheung, Yingfei Xiong, Lu Zhang, An Empirical Study on TensorFlow Program Bugs Proceedings of the 27th ACM SIGSOFT International Symposium on Software Testing and Analysis, 2018.

Sifis Lagouvardos, Julian Dolby, Neville Grech, Anastasios Antoniadis, Yannis Smaragdakis, Static Analysis of Shape in TensorFlow Programs, 34th European Conference on Object-Oriented Programming, 2020.
OpenAI et al. 2023. Gpt-4 technical report. (2023). arXiv: 2303.08774 [cs.CL].
